title: Qemu / KVM virtual machines
agents: linux
catalog: app/virtualization
license: GPL
distribution: kuhn-ruess
description:
 Monitors QEMU and libvirt-managed KVM virtual machines via the agent plugin
 'qemu', which uses virsh to enumerate running guests and reports CPU and
 memory usage per VM. The check produces one service per running VM.

 Optional upper levels on CPU and memory usage are configurable via the rule
 'Qemu / KVM'. If a discovered VM is not running, the service goes CRIT.

inventory:
 One service per running VM is created.
